author: David Greenwald | The Oregonian/OregonLive
title: NE Portland shooting injures at least one
text:
At least one person was hurt in a shooting in Northeast Portland early Saturday morning, according to KOIN .
The shooting reportedly occurred on the 4400 block of Northeast 122nd Ave. around midnight. At least 20 police units and 6 medical units, including paramedics and firefighters, reportedly responded to a 911 call from the scene.
Police have yet to release further information on the incident.
